<refnamediv>
<refname>npm-prefix</refname>
<refpurpose>Display prefix</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
<cmdsynopsis>
  <command>npm</command>    <arg choice='plain'><replaceable>prefix</replaceable></arg>
    <arg choice='opt'>-g </arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>Print the local prefix to standard out. This is the closest parent directory
to contain a package.json file unless <option>-g</option> is also specified.</para>

<para>If <option>-g</option> is specified, this will be the value of the global prefix. See
npm help 7 <emphasis remap='B'>npm-config</emphasis> for more detail.</para>
</refsect1>

